description.0: Foggy Nelson—caught and injured in the line of justice! The Black Widow helps Daredevil in his case.
description.1: It's a new career for Iron Man! But Erwin and Rhodey's enterprise in high-tech electronics leads to extreme danger. Plus what happens to Tony Stark?
description.4: Reed Richards has gone missing! The FF's remaining members must track down their leader!
description.5: Scott and Madelyne's honeymoon takes a turn when their plane goes down in the Pacific. Meanwhile, Wolverine uncovers a plot that sees Mariko undermining her clan's honor.
description.6: Dinner and a Catfight! Spider-Man and Black Cat take on the Hobgoblin. But is the Cat ready for major league crime fighting?
description.8: Who are the “Super Boxers”? Find out in this special mag, True Believers!
description.10: A flashback sequence involving an old friend of Luke's from the planet of ice, Hoth.
description.11: Spider-Man tracks Nose Norton and discovers a mischievous plot of thievery! And when the wall-crawler uncovers the criminal's hideout, Thunderball emerges!
description.12: The Vision speaks! With the help of Starfox's home technology, the Avengers aid their robotic teammate in recovering from his epic battle against Annihilus! Meanwhile, Moonstone grows stronger, using her telepathic abilities to turn Blackout into her mind puppet.
description.13: Once in the future, Captain America joins the Redeemers and spring into action to stop Hellinger's plans to destroy the rest of the world's population! Can Cap save the world and change his future? Find out in the epic conclusion to Cap's most exciting adventure yet!
description.16: Wonder Man and Spider-Man are both down on their luck and looking for a way to make some money, but volunteering for experimental weapons testing might end up killing the two heroes before they can cash their first check!
description.17: It's Strange, Blade, King, and Wong against the master of all bloodsuckers: Dracula!
description.21: The Rebels travel to Endor to deactivate the Death Star II's deflector shield, while Luke Skywalker tells Leia Organa of her true heritage.
description.22: With his powers slowly being siphoned, the weakening Iron Fist must face and defeat Master Khan to save Misty Knight and David Griffith!
description.24: Not only does Walt Simonson storm onto THOR, bringing doom, gloom and a horse-faced Thunder God with him, he smashes cover image expectations. THOR #337 sets a new standard for iconic, eye-catching covers.
description.26: Back in Manhattan, Thing is randomly attacked by heroes like Wonder Man, She-Hulk, Spider-Man…and even civilians! This can be the work of only one menace - the Puppet Master!
description.27: Iron Man, James Rhodes, is unwittingly pitted in a conflict between two divine forces- the Deviants and the Eternals!
description.31: A new love interest sweeps into Dazzler’s life just as she hits it big with a top-selling record!
description.32: Luke Skywalker returns to Dagobah while Emperor Palpatine plots to bring him to the dark side of the Force.
description.33: The theft at the Rand-Meachum Plant and the reemergence of Shades and Comanche are all related…but how?
description.34: The Watcher presents a tale in which Spider-Man and his friends daydream! What do their dreams reveal about their character, desires and ambitions? And what can these daydreams tell us about the future?
description.35: It's the Avengers versus Electro, Blackout, Moonstone, and Rhino! Read to witness the explosive conclusion! Plus: Find out why Spider-Man must decline his invitation to join the Avengers, Earth's Mightiest Heroes!
description.36: After an epic battle in the present time, 1983, Cap travels to the future with Deathlok to save the world! But when Deathlok tells Cap his world is a result of a mysterious happening in the 1983, Cap must act fast to stop it!
description.37: Cloak and Dagger's war on drugs and crime is in full swing. But are the police keen on letting the heroes of darkness and light continue to battle crime with their unorthodox methods? Plus, Cloak's hunger grows-what can sustain him now?
description.38: Appearing for one issue only-the songstress who will melt your heart and shatter your wine glass. We mean none other than Leia Organa, "Chanteuse of the Stars." The rebel alliance may hinge on her ability to entertain a group of Ambassadors, and with her singing voice, the Rebels may have to throw down their arms and surrender!
description.39: Stan will need his soapbox for this one! Read an in-depth interview with Stan Lee, the foundational creator behind Marvel’s House of Ideas.
description.41: The hour of “Redemption” is at hand for Bullseye!
description.42: What may be the most offbeat Iron Man story ever? One man battles to save a universe, while another fights to save an empty cardboard box.
description.44: Sue, Johnny and Ben battle Tyros alongside the Silver Surfer! Meanwhile, Namor the Sub-Mariner faces grave danger at Avengers Mansion.
description.45: At the mansion, the X-Men throw down with Dark Phoenix! Plus, an X-marriage!
description.53: Thing and Lockjaw teleport to the town of Rock Hollow, where a mutant boy and his mother face persecution from angry townsfolk!
description.56: Who, or what, is the Dark Wind? Daredevil tries to track down answers, but comes up short.
description.57: As Tony Stark finds himself in a strange city with no memory of how he got there, Rhodey discovers that he enjoys more and more the power of the Iron Man armor.
description.59: Sif's heart is broken as she returns to Asgard alone from the wedding of Jane and Keith. But the goddess is not the only one disturbed by the Thunder God's choices...
description.61: A battle breaks out between Tyros and Ben! A pregnant Sue is presented with an ultimatum...by Doctor Doom!
description.62: Binary joins the Starjammers! Meanwhile, a spat between Scott Summer and Madelyne Pryor leads to a confrontation with...Dark Phoenix?!
description.67: The inside story on the X-Men and the Micronauts limited series!
description.68: Darth Vader checks on the status of the Death Star II while the Rebels attempt to rescue Han Solo from Jabba the Hutt.
description.69: Shades and Comanche are back with a vengeance for Luke Cage. Iron Fist also has his own score to settle at the Rand-Meachum plant after noticing something peculiar.
description.70: Spider-Man, Cloak and Dagger & the New Mutants team-up to take down a whole horde of villains!
description.71: Lando Calrissian and Mon are trapped in the Empire-controlled citadel of Gamander. And their lives may depend on the strangest undercover agent of all-R2-D2.
description.72: After experimenting with the Osborn formula that gave the original Green Goblin his powers, Hobgoblin becomes a force to be reckoned with! Seeking out Spider-Man to "teach him the meaning of fear," the Hobgoblin wreaks havoc in Times Square! During the battle, Spidey uncovers a mystery!
description.73: Spider-Man is back! Seeking an above minimum wage job, New York's friendly neighborhood spider joins the Earth's Mightiest Heroes! Plus: Blackout, unleashed!
description.74: Traveling back in time from a dystopian future of 1991, Luther Manning arrives in the present day to find the lost Deathlok. Can Captain America aid him in finding the lost soldier before Manning draws any more attention to himself?
description.77: As Dracula's power grows, Strange and his allies must contend with cult members at every turn!
description.82: When Quicksilver decides that he will expose his daughter Luna to the Terrigen Mists, her desperate mother Crystal seeks the aid of the Thing. Lockjaw acts inexplicably.
description.83: Spider-Man teams up with the Fantastic Four as they go toe-to-toe with the villainous Dr. Faustus!
description.86: Dazzler meets Lois’ father under unfortunate circumstances. Angel gets caught up in the sisters’ legal troubles, while Rogue makes her final move.
description.88: The Hobgoblin and his gang are stealing chemicals from Osborn Industries! Outnumbered by nearly a dozen criminals, Spidey must overcome the odds and prevent the Hobgoblin from harnessing the power of a more formidable foe! Spider-Man's brute strength is tested in this action-packed issue!
description.89: The Wizard has escaped from prison! Who will survive his Mansion of Mechanized Mayhem!
description.90: One of Cap's sharpest opponents, the Porcupine, returns! Plus: the shocking outcome of Patriot's losing battle with cancer!
description.95: The search for Han Solo is cut short as the rebels find themselves facing death on a planet of Water Breathers.
description.96: It’s a street-level spotlight on Cloak and Dagger, two of the newest heroes to the Marvel Comics scene. Or at least “new” back in 1983!
description.97: In a home invasion, Danny is attacked by Meachum’s men and Fera - who makes this fight personal! In Times Square, will Luke’s recent retirement hinder him from helping an elderly woman in peril?
description.98: Yuriko helps Daredevil in his quest against Dark Wind! Plus, a major development for Bullseye.
description.99: It had to happen. It was inevitable. And yet, nobody can be truly prepared for it as Tony Stark, driven to the edge by alcoholism and the loss of his company, finally hits bottom.

2.text: The Nova Romans think Wolfsbane is the descendant of Julius Caesar and the she-wolf who raised Romulus and Remus! Still, all is not well for the New Mutants, and one of their allies will never be the same...but perhaps for the better!

3.text: WHAT IF…THE INVISIBLE GIRL HAD DIED? Sue dies giving birth while Reed takes his revenge on Annihilus.

9.text: Crossfire is revealed to be the mastermind behind Cross Tech's recent violence. Hawkeye and Mockingbird are as good as gone, unless they can escape the villain's Undertaker Machine! Mind games ensue as Hawkeye faces permanent hearing damage, and Mockingbird acknowledges her love. The issue that cemented Hawkeye and Mockingbird as an item!

15.text: In this corner, standing 6'2" and weighing in at 240 lbs., the Falcon! His foe? A mighty robot Sentinel, 20 feet tall and tipping the scales at just over several hundred tons! Place your bets!

18.text: Trouble in S.H.I.E.L.D.! The New Defenders' trip to the global peacekeeping agency goes awry when a top-secret specimen breaks loose - and it's angry!

22.text: The Power Crystal of Quon bears ill tidings for Iron Fist when it lands Danny in a coma. The Heroes for Hire assemble their allies…and take on Master Khan!

23.text: Kate reveals herself to be an Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.!

24.text: Nick Fury asks Thor's aid in investigating an alien ship heading for Earth. Thor arrives and triggers the awakening of an alien protector, Beta Ray Bill. But when Bill bests Thor and takes up his hammer, he is summoned to Asgard by Odin!

Not only does Walt Simonson storm onto THOR, bringing doom, gloom and a horse-faced Thunder God with him, he smashes cover image expectations. THOR #337 sets a new standard for iconic, eye-catching covers.

Nick Fury asks Thor's aid in investigating an alien ship heading for earth; Thor arrives and triggers the awakening of an alien protector, Bet Ray Bill; Bill bests Thor and takes up his hammer only to be accidentally summoned to Asgard by Odin who thinks he is summoning Thor.

25.text: Can Alpha Flight save Marrina from the clutches of the Master of the World, even with the help of the Sub-Mariner and Invisible Girl? And can Aurora be cured of her fractured personalities?

26.text: Back in Manhattan, Thing is randomly attacked by heroes like Wonder Man, She-Hulk, Spider-Man…and even civilians! This can be the work of only one menace - the Puppet Master!

27.text: Iron Man, James Rhodes, is unwittingly pitted in a conflict between two divine forces- the Deviants and the Eternals!

29.text: Black Widow is back on her home turf to track a missing comrade! Digital issue omits "Kaa's Hunting", published in Marvel Illustrated: Jungle Book (2007) #1.

30.text: Out with the old. Meet the BRAND NEW Defenders!

33.text: The theft at the Rand-Meachum Plant and the reemergence of Shades and Comanche are all related…but how?

37.text: Cloak and Dagger's war on drugs and crime is in full swing. But are the police keen on letting the heroes of darkness and light continue to battle crime with their unorthodox methods? Plus, Cloak's hunger grows-what can sustain him now?

Cloak and Dagger's war on drugs and crime is in full swing. But are the police keen on letting the heroes of darkness and light continue to battle crime with their unorthodox methods? Plus, Cloak's hunger grows-what can sustain him now?

40.text: It’s a throw down at Grand Central, as Hawkeye and Mockingbird take on Cross' hired goons; enter Oddball and Bombshell, two destructive villains too nefarious for words! What happens when our heroes are overpowered by the baddies?

43.text: The New Mutants are captured by Roman legionnaires, taken to Nova Roma, and drugged! The auction blocks await Wolfsbane and Psyche, but for Cannonball and Sunspot - it's the arena!

47.text: Forget what you thought you knew about Sam Wilson a.k.a. The Falcon. Things are about to get real in the Bronx!

51.text: Spider-Ham leads a jam-packed issue of animal heroes in the mighty Marvel manner. Thrill to see all your favorite heroes in action including Hulk Bunny and Goose Rider!

52.text: Moon Knight’s hands are tied when he must decide on eliminating a pack of forcibly drugged teens with superhuman strength…or protecting one of his closest friends.

53.text: Thing and Lockjaw teleport to the town of Rock Hollow, where a mutant boy and his mother face persecution from angry townsfolk!

54.text: M.O.D.O.K. and General Ross strike a deal that results in the Abomination destroying the Hulk!

55.text: Alpha Flight has set off to find fellow teammate Marrina, but what will become of them when they find a nefarious foe who professes to be the Master of the World?

58.text: The team accompanies Sunspot's mother on an expedition into the Amazon. But things get hairy when they're ambushed by Amazonian women! What business does the Hellfire Club have in the Amazon?

60.text: WHAT IF…SUB-MARINER HAD SAVED ATLANTIS FROM ITS DESTINY? Namor defeats Destiny who attempts to destroy Atlantis, gets accused of murder, recovers Neptune's trident, and fights Attuma for Atlantis' freedom.

63.text: The Punisher stands trial for his crimes.

69.text: Shades and Comanche are back with a vengeance for Luke Cage. Iron Fist also has his own score to settle at the Rand-Meachum plant after noticing something peculiar.

70.text: Spider-Man, Cloak and Dagger & the New Mutants team-up to take down a whole horde of villains!

75.text: Cloak and Dagger, who wield the powers of darkness and light, set out to fight crime in New York City. But when a stray bullet from a street battle gone wrong harms a civilian, the superhuman duo may be forced to question their vigilante methodology...

78.text: Check out the Defenders as they take on the 24th century! The future is truly wild!

79.text: Hawkeye and Mockingbird grow closer in the wake of Sheila Danning's betrayal. Who is Bobbi Morse, former S.H.I.E.L.D. agent turned super hero? The Silencer returns to stop Clint and Bobbi's investigation into Cross Tech. Guest-starring the Sky-Cycle, Hawkeye's sweet, flying ride!

80.text: When Bruce Banner gets chummy with his new research assistant, Dr. Kate Waynesboro, Banner's Recordasphere gets extremely jealous and sets out to destroy the friendship!

81.text: Amphibious Alpha Flight member Marrina has gone feral and is lashing out at the rest of the team. What is causing her unexpected behavior?

82.text: When Quicksilver decides that he will expose his daughter Luna to the Terrigen Mists, her desperate mother Crystal seeks the aid of the Thing. Lockjaw acts inexplicably.

84.text: The Black Widow spins a web of intrigue in a four-part epic! Natasha must locate her companion Ivan, and turns to S.H.I.E.L.D. for an alliance. Digital issue omits "How Fear Came", published in Marvel Illustrated: Jungle Book (2007) #1.

85.text: The Elf sends the Defenders off on a mission of interdimensional conquest!

87.text: Enthralled in his relationship, Clint opens up to new girlfriend Sheila Danning about his super hero origin. The date ends abruptly when Hawkeye investigates a break-in at Cross Technologies…and the intruder’s none other than Mockingbird! Is Cross Tech involved in illegal affairs that are destroying the environment? Mockingbird seems to think so, and she'll stop at nothing to convince Hawkeye!

94.text: Joy Mercado’s investigation of Druid Walsh heats up in “Exploding Myths”!

97.text: In a home invasion, Danny is attacked by Meachum’s men and Fera - who makes this fight personal! In Times Square, will Luke’s recent retirement hinder him from helping an elderly woman in peril?
